               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1288" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1288" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1288" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1288" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Charles Davis; we live in Cornwall-road, Lambeth; the prisoner worked with my husband. I put a sovereign and a half-sovereign into a box on the 27th of Sept.—the prisoner, my little girl, and the other children, were in the room—I went away, leaving the prisoner in the room—I afterwards missed the money—I found the prisoner at the Surrey theatre at one o'clock in the morning.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1289" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1289" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1289" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1289" type="given" value="SARAH ANN"></interp>SARAH ANN DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the room when the money was put there—the children were going to school—the prisoner told me to go and open the door, and when I came in I saw him putting up the box that the money was in—he walked up and down the room three times, and then he said, "I will go and buy a halfpenny-worth of apples"—he went out, and did not return—he ought to have come back to work—no one else came in but my mother, which was in about an hour and a half afterwards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1290" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1290" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1290" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1290" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 130.) I took the prisoner—he said he had never seen any of the money, and if he had, if there was no money found on him, we could do nothing with him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I did not have it; I did not know it was there.</p>
